==English==
===Noun===
'''grandstand'''
# The seating area at a stadium or arena.
# The audience at a public event.

===Verb===
'''to grandstand'''
# ''(intransitive)'' To behave dramatically or showily to impress an audience or observers.
#* ''Many politicians prefer to '''grandstand''' on hot-button issues rather than enact tough policy changes.''
